===Etymology===
Named after [[Oedipus]] in Greek Mythology, who unwittingly killed his father and married his mother.

===Pronunciation===
*[[w:International Phonetic Alphabet|IPA]]:/idəpɛs kɒmplɛks/

===Noun===
'''Oedipus complex'''

# (In [[Freudian]] theory) The [[complex]] of [[emotion]]s aroused in a [[child]] by and [[unconscious]] [[sexual]] [[desire]] for the [[parent]] of the opposite sex.

